♪ Ride it, my pony ♪

511
00:20:49,567 --> 00:20:53,470
♪ My saddle's waiting ♪

512
00:20:53,504 --> 00:20:56,306
♪ Come and jump on it ♪

513
00:20:56,340 --> 00:20:58,742
♪ If you want it ♪

514
00:20:58,776 --> 00:21:00,677
♪ Let's do it ♪

515
00:21:00,711 --> 00:21:03,146
♪ Ride it, my pony ♪

516
00:21:03,180 --> 00:21:07,817
♪ My saddle's waiting ♪

517
00:21:07,852 --> 00:21:10,754
♪ Come and jump on it ♪

518
00:21:10,788 --> 00:21:13,723
♪ Yeah. ♪

519
00:21:15,893 --> 00:21:17,527
All right, Artie!

520
00:21:17,562 --> 00:21:18,762
That was... that was fun.

521
00:21:18,796 --> 00:21:20,063
Thank you. (Chuckles)

522
00:21:20,097 --> 00:21:22,566
- Ginuwine is a badass.
- Artie, that was

523
00:21:22,600 --> 00:21:24,200
r-really, really good.

524
00:21:24,235 --> 00:21:25,702
I had no idea.

525
00:21:25,736 --> 00:21:27,437
- Really?
- Seriously.

526
00:21:27,471 --> 00:21:29,471
That's the best voice
I have ever heard.

527
00:21:31,776 --> 00:21:34,611
(school bell ringing)

528
00:21:39,150 --> 00:21:40,250
Brad.

529
00:21:40,284 --> 00:21:41,952
Welcome, everybody!

530
00:21:41,986 --> 00:21:44,387
Can I just say
what an awesome job

531
00:21:44,422 --> 00:21:47,891
you all did in your auditions.
I was... I was blown away.

532
00:21:47,925 --> 00:21:49,759
Okay, so...

533
00:21:49,794 --> 00:21:52,629
grab a pair of gloves
and some sheet music.

534
00:21:52,663 --> 00:21:55,098
"S-S-S..." "Sit Down,
You're Rockin' the Boat"

535
00:21:55,132 --> 00:21:57,467
by the legendary Frank Loesser.

536
00:21:57,501 --> 00:21:58,869
We did this at
McKinley's Christmas concert

537
00:21:58,903 --> 00:22:00,904
my sophomore year,
and we got a standing O.

538
00:22:00,938 --> 00:22:03,440
Artie, why don't
you take the lead.

539
00:22:03,474 --> 00:22:04,808
- Yes!
- Mr. Schuester.

540
00:22:04,842 --> 00:22:06,276
With all due respect,

541
00:22:06,310 --> 00:22:07,711
I'm the only member here who was

542
00:22:07,745 --> 00:22:09,246
in Mr. Ryerson's
original Glee Club;

543
00:22:09,280 --> 00:22:11,147
therefore, I should be
getting the first solo.

544
00:22:11,182 --> 00:22:13,049
Say what?

545
00:22:13,084 --> 00:22:15,485
It's the first song; it sets
the precedent for everything.

546
00:22:15,520 --> 00:22:17,787
Rachel, Artie's gonna
sing the first solo, period.

547
00:22:17,822 --> 00:22:19,502
You and everyone else
are gonna have plenty

548
00:22:19,523 --> 00:22:22,092
of opportunities for a
solo; we'll all take turns.

549
00:22:22,126 --> 00:22:24,127
In fact, I was thinking
for sectionals, we would do

550
00:22:24,161 --> 00:22:26,930
a medley from<i> Grease.</i>
Who wants the Sandy part?

551
00:22:26,964 --> 00:22:28,832
Is this even a
discussion right now?!

552
00:22:28,866 --> 00:22:30,834
I'm the only person in this room
who can play Sandy!

553
00:22:30,868 --> 00:22:33,069
- Why? Because you're white?
- RACHEL: Okay, I wouldn't dream

554
00:22:33,104 --> 00:22:36,106
of being Mrs. Saigon
or black Dorothy from the Wiz,

555
00:22:36,140 --> 00:22:38,620
but if we want to be taken
seriously as a glee club,

556
00:22:38,643 --> 00:22:40,176
then it can't be about color
or disability or whatever.

557
00:22:40,211 --> 00:22:42,245
It has to be about who
has the best voice.

558
00:22:42,280 --> 00:22:44,281
Exactly. That would be me.

559
00:22:47,351 --> 00:22:48,418
Let's warm up.

560
00:22:48,452 --> 00:22:49,692
Brad.

561
00:22:52,723 --> 00:22:54,724
(vacuum whirring)

562
00:22:59,530 --> 00:23:01,064
(vacuum stops)

563
00:23:04,502 --> 00:23:05,969
I thought you were
finishing up out here?

564
00:23:06,003 --> 00:23:08,004
I-I was just taking
a little break.

565
00:23:08,039 --> 00:23:09,399
You just left
the vacuum cleaner on

566
00:23:09,407 --> 00:23:10,807
so that I would think
you were cleaning

567
00:23:10,842 --> 00:23:12,442
while you were goofing off
with the sheet music.

568
00:23:12,476 --> 00:23:15,278
(sighs) There is a division
of labor in this house, Will.

569
00:23:15,313 --> 00:23:16,813
You do the cooking and cleaning,

570
00:23:16,848 --> 00:23:18,815
and I will carry our children
when we have them.

571
00:23:18,850 --> 00:23:20,517
Which might not be anytime soon

572
00:23:20,551 --> 00:23:22,485
because I'm sure all this
extra free work you're doing

573
00:23:22,520 --> 00:23:24,020
for the Glee Club
is tiring you out

574
00:23:24,055 --> 00:23:25,789
and making your sperm stressed.

575
00:23:25,823 --> 00:23:27,190
You're right.

576
00:23:27,225 --> 00:23:29,192
I am stressed.

577
00:23:29,227 --> 00:23:32,028
And I'm sure my sperm's stressed, too.
Mm-hmm.

578
00:23:32,063 --> 00:23:34,130
The Glee Club is one day old,
and there's already in-fighting.

579
00:23:34,165 --> 00:23:36,733
(sighs) Which is
kind of my fault,

580
00:23:36,767 --> 00:23:38,368
because I asked
who wanted the first solo,

581
00:23:38,402 --> 00:23:40,337
and Rachel and Mercedes
both raised their hands,

582
00:23:40,371 --> 00:23:41,838
and I don't want to
disappoint either of them.

583
00:23:41,873 --> 00:23:43,874
Just give it to whichever one
is the most pathetic.

584
00:23:43,908 --> 00:23:46,309
It's much harder to be jealous
of someone when you think

585
00:23:46,344 --> 00:23:47,911
you're better than they are.

586
00:23:47,945 --> 00:23:49,813
Even if they get something
that you want.

587
00:23:49,847 --> 00:23:51,414
I love it when you're all smart.

588
00:23:51,449 --> 00:23:53,016
Oh. (Giggles)

589
00:23:55,953 --> 00:23:58,421
I'm only gonna
ask you this once,

590
00:23:58,456 --> 00:24:01,725
and then I promise I will never
bring up the Glee Club again.

591
00:24:01,759 --> 00:24:04,060
Okay.

592
00:24:04,095 --> 00:24:06,229
Is it worth it?

593
00:24:06,264 --> 00:24:07,864
I mean, you know
I'm a little bit psychic.

594
00:24:07,899 --> 00:24:09,566
I have a bad feeling about this.

595
00:24:09,600 --> 00:24:12,369
How could anything bad
come out of a glee club?

596
00:24:12,403 --> 00:24:14,571
Because look how distracted
you are by it already.

597
00:24:14,605 --> 00:24:17,374
What if you end up spending
so much time with the glee kids

598
00:24:17,408 --> 00:24:19,376
that you start neglecting
our time together?

599
00:24:19,410 --> 00:24:21,211
I don't want to become
one of those ignored wives

600
00:24:21,245 --> 00:24:22,279
who has an affair.

601
00:24:22,313 --> 00:24:24,915
You are the love of my life.

602
00:24:24,949 --> 00:24:28,385
And nothing is ever gonna
take you away from me.

603
00:24:32,557 --> 00:24:34,157
Good.

604
00:24:35,455 --> 00:24:37,589
Mr. Schuester, how's the search for
our male lead going?

605
00:24:37,623 --> 00:24:40,392
I took the initiative of making
a list of potential candidates

606
00:24:40,426 --> 00:24:41,893
- based on their yearbook photos.
- Um, thanks, Rachel.

607
00:24:41,928 --> 00:24:43,762
But I was actually headed
to the locker room

608
00:24:43,796 --> 00:24:46,098
- to see if, uh, any of the football
players signed up. - Great.

609
00:24:46,132 --> 00:24:47,532
I also made a list
of all the reasons

610
00:24:47,567 --> 00:24:49,034
why I should be getting
the first solo.

611
00:24:49,068 --> 00:24:50,402
I think it would make
an important statement

612
00:24:50,436 --> 00:24:51,937
to the rest of the team
if you told them

613
00:24:51,971 --> 00:24:54,451
right at the beginning
that I'm the star.

614
00:24:55,241 --> 00:24:57,709
Oh, my God.

615
00:24:57,744 --> 00:24:59,077
A-Are you okay?

616
00:24:59,112 --> 00:25:01,213
(laughter)

617
00:25:01,247 --> 00:25:03,215
I told you.

618
00:25:03,249 --> 00:25:05,417
Everyone hates me.

619
00:25:05,451 --> 00:25:07,219
(school bell ringing)

620
00:25:07,253 --> 00:25:08,820
Everybody up!

621
00:25:08,855 --> 00:25:10,622
We're moving to the auditorium.

622
00:25:10,657 --> 00:25:11,990
Alcoholics Anonymous
has the auditorium.

623
00:25:12,025 --> 00:25:13,291
Not anymore.

624
00:25:13,326 --> 00:25:15,060
Principal Figgins
believes in us so much,

625
00:25:15,094 --> 00:25:16,294
he's giving it to us.

626
00:25:16,329 --> 00:25:18,096
For a while.

627
00:25:18,131 --> 00:25:20,966
Let's go. And grab a copy of
"You're the One That I Want."

628
00:25:21,000 --> 00:25:22,467
Hold up, who gets
to sing the Sandy part?

629
00:25:22,502 --> 00:25:24,036
Rachel.

630
00:25:25,104 --> 00:25:26,672
Are you serious?

631
00:25:26,706 --> 00:25:29,107
I can blow the roof
off that auditorium.

632
00:25:29,142 --> 00:25:30,742
Her little bitty Jewish voice
won't make it

633
00:25:30,777 --> 00:25:32,511
- past the third row.
- Racist!

634
00:25:32,545 --> 00:25:34,946
And untrue. I can belt just
as good as you, better even.

635
00:25:34,981 --> 00:25:36,948
Oh, really?
Well, let's prove it.

636
00:25:36,983 --> 00:25:39,484
Let's have a sing-off
right here, right now.

637
00:25:39,519 --> 00:25:41,253
We're not having a sing-off!

638
00:25:41,287 --> 00:25:43,255
Although that's not a bad idea
for a future exercise.

639
00:25:43,289 --> 00:25:45,357
Rachel has this solo.

640
00:25:45,391 --> 00:25:46,658
Like I said,
you'll all take turns.

641
00:25:46,693 --> 00:25:48,627
Except the white girl
goes first.

642
00:25:48,661 --> 00:25:50,696
The white girl
always goes first.

643
00:25:50,730 --> 00:25:52,164
(sobbing softly)

644
00:25:58,204 --> 00:26:00,205
Hey.

645
00:26:03,343 --> 00:26:05,344
I didn't get the solo.

646
00:26:07,347 --> 00:26:11,717
I lost it to that demented
little Beanie Baby.

647
00:26:11,751 --> 00:26:15,187
Mr. Schuester is never
gonna give me a solo.

648
00:26:15,221 --> 00:26:17,389
It's a waste of time;
I'm gonna quit.

649
00:26:17,423 --> 00:26:20,726
Nobody in there is gonna see me
the way that I see myself.

650
00:26:20,760 --> 00:26:22,728
Mercedes.

651
00:26:22,762 --> 00:26:24,029
You are so young.

652
00:26:24,063 --> 00:26:26,331
Glee Club just started.

653
00:26:26,333 --> 00:26:28,467
Who knows
what your future holds?

654
00:26:28,501 --> 00:26:30,969
Mercedes,

655
00:26:31,004 --> 00:26:34,206
you are a star.

656
00:26:34,240 --> 00:26:36,208
But part of the responsibility

657
00:26:36,242 --> 00:26:38,176
that goes along
with being a star

658
00:26:38,211 --> 00:26:41,246
is learning to share
the spotlight.

659
00:26:41,281 --> 00:26:45,150
Maybe she's gonna get the solos

660
00:26:45,184 --> 00:26:47,486
because she needs it more
than you do right now.

661
00:26:47,520 --> 00:26:51,189
Truth is, Mercedes, Rachel
will make you better.

662
00:26:51,224 --> 00:26:53,425
Her drive and ambition

663
00:26:53,459 --> 00:26:56,261
will help you raise
your expectations of yourself,

664
00:26:56,296 --> 00:26:58,730
and you can use that
to become great.

665
00:26:58,765 --> 00:27:00,732
And I have a feeling

666
00:27:00,767 --> 00:27:02,868
you two are gonna
become great friends.

667
00:27:02,902 --> 00:27:04,202
(scoffs)

668
00:27:04,237 --> 00:27:05,937
(sniffles)

669
00:27:05,972 --> 00:27:08,440
Stars have a way
of finding each other.

670
00:27:08,474 --> 00:27:10,309
Okay, come here.

671
00:27:12,312 --> 00:27:14,279
(school bell ringing)

672
00:27:14,314 --> 00:27:15,547
There you go, Sue.

673
00:27:15,581 --> 00:27:16,949
Some principals would say

674
00:27:16,983 --> 00:27:20,052
that importing a rare silk
trampoline mat

675
00:27:20,086 --> 00:27:23,622
from China is an extravagance,
but not this principal.

676
00:27:23,656 --> 00:27:26,858
The Cheerios! Are McKinley
High's number one priority.

677
00:27:26,893 --> 00:27:29,094
Oh, thank you so much,
Principal Figgins.

678
00:27:29,128 --> 00:27:30,762
I could have never
led my Cheerios!

679
00:27:30,797 --> 00:27:34,399
To a record five consecutive
national championships

680
00:27:34,434 --> 00:27:36,301
without you.
(chuckles)

681
00:27:36,336 --> 00:27:38,303
Actually, I could have done it
very easily without you.

682
00:27:38,338 --> 00:27:40,619
Oh, uh, and that reminds me.
I have a question for you.

683
00:27:40,640 --> 00:27:42,040
Hmm?

684
00:27:42,075 --> 00:27:43,909
What exactly is going on
with Will Schuester

685
00:27:43,943 --> 00:27:45,377
taking over the show choir?

686
00:27:45,411 --> 00:27:47,212
The Glee Club?

687
00:27:47,246 --> 00:27:49,915
Why, Sue, that's nothing
but a trifling.

688
00:27:49,949 --> 00:27:51,917
Well, I just want to be clear
that the star performers

689
00:27:51,951 --> 00:27:53,919
at this high school
are my Cheerios!,

690
00:27:53,953 --> 00:27:55,821
and I should hope
it remains that way.

691
00:27:55,855 --> 00:27:57,456
Oh, Sue, don't worry.

692
00:27:57,490 --> 00:28:00,926
You are my star.
You are on Fox Sports Net.

693
00:28:00,960 --> 00:28:02,894
- Yes. - And besides, show
choir won't last.

694
00:28:02,929 --> 00:28:06,598
Will only has five students,
one of them a cripple.

695
00:28:06,633 --> 00:28:08,767
And children these days
aren't interested

696
00:28:08,801 --> 00:28:11,136
in singing to each other.

697
00:28:11,170 --> 00:28:14,239
They're too busy with
their Friendster and Myspace

698
00:28:14,274 --> 00:28:15,741
and Blockbuster Video.

699
00:28:15,775 --> 00:28:17,676
These are things
that are here to stay.

700
00:28:17,710 --> 00:28:19,411
Well, I don't know.

701
00:28:19,445 --> 00:28:23,248
I have a bad feeling
about this Glee Club.

702
00:28:23,283 --> 00:28:25,550
(school bell ringing)

703
00:28:27,820 --> 00:28:29,621
(cheering)

704
00:28:31,624 --> 00:28:33,125
Come on, go!

705
00:28:33,159 --> 00:28:34,593
Okay, come on.

706
00:28:34,627 --> 00:28:36,495
Traveling.

707
00:28:36,529 --> 00:28:38,931
Hey!

708
00:28:38,965 --> 00:28:40,933
Hey, you know, because
we're best friends,

709
00:28:40,967 --> 00:28:43,001
I want to ask you something frankly.
Sure.

710
00:28:43,036 --> 00:28:44,436
Wait, I-I'm your
best friend?

711
00:28:44,470 --> 00:28:46,638
I-I know nothing about you.
We hardly even talk.

712
00:28:46,673 --> 00:28:48,440
We just play basketball
once a week.

713
00:28:48,474 --> 00:28:50,208
Yeah, like I said, best friends.

714
00:28:50,243 --> 00:28:51,443
(sighs)

715
00:28:51,477 --> 00:28:53,278
What are your...
Thank you.

716
00:28:53,313 --> 00:28:55,280
What are your intentions
with this Glee Club?

717
00:28:55,315 --> 00:28:56,481
Intentions?
I don't know.

718
00:28:56,516 --> 00:28:58,150
I guess we'll have to find out.

719
00:28:58,184 --> 00:28:59,551
I don't know, I just...

720
00:28:59,586 --> 00:29:01,553
I look around this school,
I see all these kids

721
00:29:01,588 --> 00:29:02,988
who don't have the arts
in their lives,

722
00:29:03,022 --> 00:29:04,990
and I want them
to have what I had...

723
00:29:05,024 --> 00:29:07,392
A place where they can go
to experience the joy of music.

724
00:29:07,427 --> 00:29:09,161
Yeah, well, they already
have that, William.

725
00:29:09,195 --> 00:29:11,396
It's called the iPod.
I don't know, being a part

726
00:29:11,431 --> 00:29:13,465
of Glee Club was the best thing
that ever happened to me.

727
00:29:13,499 --> 00:29:15,400
Now you're a high school
Spanish teacher.

728
00:29:15,435 --> 00:29:16,668
(laughs)

729
00:29:16,703 --> 00:29:18,470
Will, the students
at this school

730
00:29:18,504 --> 00:29:19,905
aren't going to
become performers.

731
00:29:19,939 --> 00:29:21,240
They're not gonna become
professional singers

732
00:29:21,274 --> 00:29:22,708
or dancers or actors.

733
00:29:22,742 --> 00:29:24,643
They'll be fry cooks
and auto mechanics.

734
00:29:24,677 --> 00:29:27,479
And it's really unfair of you
to suggest anything otherwise.

735
00:29:27,513 --> 00:29:31,250
Fostering unrealistic dreams
in these kids will accomplish

736
00:29:31,284 --> 00:29:33,018
absolutely nothing
but to make their lives

737
00:29:33,052 --> 00:29:36,321
that much more dark
and depressing.

738
00:29:36,356 --> 00:29:39,191
I'm sorry, Sue.
I just disagree.

739
00:29:39,225 --> 00:29:41,159
I mean, the arts are important.

740
00:29:41,194 --> 00:29:43,495
Certainly more important
than cheerleading.

741
00:29:43,530 --> 00:29:44,897
(quietly):
How dare you.

742
00:29:44,931 --> 00:29:46,565
And I think,
with a little hard work,

743
00:29:46,599 --> 00:29:48,700
this Glee Club could
really accomplish something.

744
00:29:48,735 --> 00:29:50,736
I got Finn Hudson to sign up,

745
00:29:50,770 --> 00:29:53,005
and he's the captain
of the football team, so...

746
00:29:53,039 --> 00:29:54,706
who knows
what our future could hold?

747
00:29:54,741 --> 00:29:57,376
I'm gonna give you an
ultimatum, William.

748
00:29:57,410 --> 00:29:58,911
You either drop this Glee Club,

749
00:29:58,945 --> 00:30:01,213
